The Defence Headquarters (DHQ) said its air component of “Operation Gama Aiki” has neutralised several bandits at Maguga in Rafi local government area of Niger State. The Coordinator, Defence Media Operations, Major General John Enenche in a statement said the operation was executed in support of Operation Thunder Strike on 19 April 2020 sequel to reports that some armed bandits, clad in black attire, had been sighted along with a large herd of rustled cattles in the area. He said the Air Component swiftly scrambled its aircraft to attack the location. He said, “Upon sighting the approaching attack aircraft, the armed bandits scampered to conceal themselves under nearby shrubs but were engaged with cannon fire which led to the neutralisation of several of them,” The coordinator while thanking  Nigerians for their support also appealed to them to continue to provide useful information that would facilitate troops operation to restore peace and security to all affected parts of the country.  